Title: IFAA World Congress in Anatomy
Description: The International Federation of Associations of Anatomists (IFAA), which was established in 1903, is the federated body bringing together Associations of Anatomy and Anatomists from around the world. This international conference is expected to feature more than 1,500 delegates from around the world. It is held across three days, each of which will include 2 plenary speaker sessions, at least eight symposia and a poster session. The programme features an excellent line up of internationally renowned plenary speakers, in addition to a range of symposia that span the breadth of activities in the anatomical sciences.
Venue: Blue Fin Venue, 110 Southwark St, SE1 0SU
